Market-Based Rate Tariff
1. Availability: Electricity Maine, LLC (Seller) makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff for wholesale sales to purchasers with whom Seller has contracted.
2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all sales of electric energy and/or capacity by Seller.
3. Rates: All sales pursuant to this Tariff shall be made at rates negotiated between the purchaser and Electricity Maine, LLC.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions for purchases of electric energy and capacity shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Electricity Maine, LLC.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Sellers market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Electricity Maine to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Sellers market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Sellers market-based authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: The Commission granted Seller the following waivers and blanket authorizations: (i) waivers of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commissions regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (ii) waiver of Part 41, Part 101 with the exception that waiver of the provisions that apply to hydropower licensees has not been granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects, and Part 141 of the Commissions regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements, except for 18 C.F.R. §141.15; and (iii) blanket authorizations under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. § 824c, and Part 34 of the Commissions regulations for all future issuances of securities and assumptions of liability. Electricity Maine, LLC, Docket No. ER10-3220-000.
7. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller in all regions, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
8. This Tariff is effective upon such date as set by the Commission.
